Last updated: 2/April/2024
We are committed to protecting your privacy. We understand the importance of privacy and are dedicated to ensuring the trust and confidence of all our users. Our Privacy Policy explains the handling of information in relation to EasyQR available on the App Store.
Information We Do Not Collect
EasyQR is designed to be used without the need for data collection. As such, our app:
Does not collect, use, store, or share any personal information from its users.
Does not require users to create an account or register to use the application.
Does not use any third-party services that might access personal data.
No Data Collection
The EasyQR app does not require or allow the input, access, transmission, or storage of personal data of any kind. This means:
No personal data is collected when you download or use our app.
No device-specific information, location data, or identifiers are collected.
No data is collected in the background while using the app.
Data Security
Since our app does not collect any personal data, there is no risk of your data being lost, misused, accessed without authorization, or disclosed. Your privacy and security are preserved while using EasyQR.
Children’s Privacy
Our app is safe for all ages because it does not involve any data collection. We are committed to protecting the privacy of children and encourage parents to actively participate in their children’s online activities.
Changes to Our Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy occasionally. Such changes will be posted on this page, and we encourage you to review our Privacy Policy periodically to stay informed about how we safeguard your information.
Contact Us
If you have any questions about our Privacy Policy or data practices, please contact us at
mobilefellow@outlook.com
.
By using EasyQR, you agree to the terms of this Privacy Policy.
Disclaimer
This Privacy Policy template is provided as a resource for app developers to reference and customize for their own use. It is recommended to have a professional legal advisor review your final Privacy Policy to ensure it complies with all applicable laws and regulations.
